title: Goswami, Raj star in India's title win

title: Chance of newborn survival: Somalia better off than India

author: Stephen Leahy
description: While President Trump wants to revive America’s coal industry, India is embracing renewables, LED lighting, electric cars, and more.
title: India Launches Massive Push for Clean Power, Lighting, and Cars

description: The US-based technology major Apple has started selling iPhones at select stores in the country that were assembled in India as part of its trial run.
title: Apple selling 'Made-in-India' iPhones at select stores: Report | Gadgets Now

description: The Election Commission of India is demonstrating the working of Electronic Voting Machines and Voter Verifiable Paper Audit Trail System and is holding a press conference at Delhi's Vigyan Bhavan today. Stay with us for all updates
title: Election Commission's demonstration of the working of EVMs - The Times of India

description: ​Most African students in Ahmedabad feel that Gujaratis could teach them business and entrepreneurship skills. Africans also feel that, while Indians are doing business in their country, African businessmen in India are almost nonexistent.​
title: Gujarat can teach Africa how to do ‘dhanda’ - Times of India

description: Pakistan Foreign Office spokesman Nafees Zakaria said that Pakistan has been underscoring for decades the risks of diversion by India of imported nuclear fuel, equipment and technology, received pursuant to civil nuclear cooperation agreements and the 2008 NSG waiver.
title: India has been diverting nuclear materials to make weapons: Pakistan - Times of India

author: Surendra Singh
description: India is still behind many Asian countries when it comes to internet speed. But things are set to change in the next 18 months when Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO) plans to usher in an age of high-speed internet in the country with the launch of three communication satellites.
title: India to enter high-speed internet era with Isro's new satellites - Times of India

description: China has been pressing for a two-step process which includes setting up criteria - a standard for admission -- for the inclusion of countries that are not signatories to the NPT. Beijing also equates India's case with Pak, which, too, has applied for the NSG membership.
title: NSG likely to meet next month, slim chance of India's entry - Times of India

author: Sanjay Dutta
description: India will flex its market muscle to secure better terms from Opec when ministers from the cartel of oil exporting countries, accounting for roughly 35% of global supplies, meet this week to discuss extending the production cut deal to prop up prices.
title: India to flex market muscle to secure better deals from shaky Opec - Times of India
